<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-10-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="274" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d274">
                    <head>No. 219.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Morgan</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-10-17"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 17,
                            1882</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 329.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                        dispatch, No. 503, of the 27th ultimo, relative to the matriculation of
                        United States citizens in Mexico, and to congratulate you upon your clear
                        and forcible presentation of the subject to the minister for foreign
                        affairs, thus strongly re-enforcing the views of this government on this
                        important matter.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>